Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(peeled and minced) until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

== Garlic Mashed Potatoes ==

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid; drain.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in empty #pot over medium heat. Add garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Add potatoes and @sour cream{2%tablespoon}; mash until smooth, adding splashes of reserved cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Rosemary Breadcrumb Brussels Sprouts ==

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring often, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer panko to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Add to bowl with toasted panko; toss to combine. Season with half the minced rosemary, salt, and pepper.

== Balsamic & Fig Beef Tenderloin ==

While Brussels sprouts roast, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot; cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}, @fig jam{2%tablespoon}, @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings), any resting juices from beef, and remaining minced rosemary to taste. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and beef between #plates{}. Top beef with sauce and serve.

> Gettin' figgy with it! Fig jam, that is. The sweet stuff is paired with balsamic vinegar to create a rich and tangy pan sauce for drizzling over beef tenderloin. Caramelized Brussels sprouts are topped with crunchy, golden rosemary breadcrumbs. This dish is bursting with flavors and textures that'll make your mouth dance.